<tr id="L134"><td><a href="#L134">134</a></td><td>ARCHER:  You're a very brave man, Malcolm. Commander Tucker's going to be fine, thanks to you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L135"><td><a href="#L135">135</a></td><td>REED:  I'm afraid I don't understand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L136"><td><a href="#L136">136</a></td><td>PHLOX:  Get some rest. There will be plenty of time to explain what happened in the morning. (the two men leave)</td></tr>

<tr id="L137"><td><a href="#L137">137</a></td><td>REED:  Sub-Commander?</td></tr>

<tr id="L138"><td><a href="#L138">138</a></td><td>T'POL:  How are you feeling?</td></tr>

<tr id="L139"><td><a href="#L139">139</a></td><td>REED:  I'd feel a lot better if I knew what was going on.</td></tr>

<tr id="L140"><td><a href="#L140">140</a></td><td>T'POL:  Captain Archer would be quite annoyed with me if I told you of your heroics. I believe he's looking forward to doing that himself in the morning.</td></tr>

<tr id="L141"><td><a href="#L141">141</a></td><td>REED:  Heroics?</td></tr>

<tr id="L142"><td><a href="#L142">142</a></td><td>T'POL:  I had no idea you could be so selfless in the face of such danger. Most males of your species would have given in to their fear.</td></tr>

<tr id="L143"><td><a href="#L143">143</a></td><td>REED:  Well, since you're obviously not going to tell me what happened I suppose a simple good night will have to do.</td></tr>

<tr id="L144"><td><a href="#L144">144</a></td><td>T'POL:  Vulcans can never ignore courage.</td></tr>

<tr id="L145"><td><a href="#L145">145</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: She sits on the bed and takes his hand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L146"><td><a href="#L146">146</a></td><td>T'POL:   And this Vulcan will never ignore Lieutenant Malcolm Reed again.</td></tr>

<tr id="L147"><td><a href="#L147">147</a></td><td>REED:  I can't say I've ever ignored you, T'Pol. Is it all right if I call you T'Pol?</td></tr>

<tr id="L148"><td><a href="#L148">148</a></td><td>T'POL:  Yes. May I call you Malcolm?</td></tr>

<tr id="L149"><td><a href="#L149">149</a></td><td>REED:  I suppose so. But, if the truth be known, I've never much cared for the name Malcolm. Always seemed a bit too stuffy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L150"><td><a href="#L150">150</a></td><td>T'POL:  I think it's a lovely name. Mol-Kom is the Vulcan word for serenity.</td></tr>

<tr id="L151"><td><a href="#L151">151</a></td><td>REED:  Well, then, perhaps I won't change it. Pity, though. I was rather growing fond of the name Stinky. I can't believe you just did that.</td></tr>

